        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 29 at 6:47PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>Temperatures have fallen to 32 degrees across portions of
Saratoga and west to northwest Rensselaer County early this
evening. Some intermittent light freezing rain or drizzle
may cause light ice accumulations on untreated surfaces.

Temperatures will start to warm back above freezing towards
midnight as a warm front begins to move back northward across
the region. The precipitation will change back to plain rain.
</description>
